dden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cpc1665702873099.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cpc1665702873099.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cpc1665702873099.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cpc1665702873099\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n ProcScript for Menus\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You control how a menu item is displayed by using the ProcScript instructions in the preDisplay trigger.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cpc1665702873099__section_w830ab1b5b1_w831ab1b5_w832ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">ProcScript Functions</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Function</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sqy1665702665979.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sqy1665702665979.html\" title=\"Return or set the checked status of a menu item.\">$check</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$check</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> places a checkmark before the menu item.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$check</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code> removes the checkmark before the menu item.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">If an icon has been defined for the menu item, the checkmark is placed over the icon.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$check</span> cannot be used in a menu bar.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"air1665702666109.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/air1665702666109.html\" title=\"Disables a menu item in a menu object.\">$disable</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$disable</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> disables the menu item.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$disable</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code> enables the menu item.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">A disabled menu item is visible but can’t be selected by the user. You\n                           can control how a disabled menu is presented in the menu properties.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sed1665702666179.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sed1665702666179.html\" title=\"Return or set the display status of a menu item.\">$hide</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$hide</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> hides the menu item.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$hide</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">False</code> shows the menu item.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bym1718980125274.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bym1718980125274.html\" title=\"Insert or retrieve one or more menu items at the location of a dynamic menu placeholder\">$inlinemenu</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e17__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Menu items of type Dynamic menu are placeholders for menus that you define using ProcScript. You assign the definition of your menu to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$inlinemenu</span>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e179\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">ProcScript Statements</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e179__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Statement</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e179__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e179__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kyz1665702608722.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kyz1665702608722.html\" title=\"Activate or load the specified menu bar.\">pulldown</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e179__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Use this statement to activate the menu when your Uniface application runs in character mode.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e179__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">pulldown/load</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cpc1665702873099__d6492e179__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Loads a new definition for the application menu bar.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/frp1665702850866.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Menu Properties</a><p>Menu properties enable you to control the appearance of menus using the font, colors, and images. They are applicable only for Windows applications and are defined by the menu logical in the [application] section of the application initialization file (usys.ini).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kdw1705579836661.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Dynamic Menu Items</a><p>Dynamic menus contain one or more menu items that are generated at runtime, and inserted in a predetermined location of a drop-down or popup menu. They can be used, for example, to display and open recently accessed objects, list and switch between currently open windows, or provide a pop-up menu that is related to the value of a field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526556\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526556\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ProcScript for Menus Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 ProcScript for Menus You control how a menu item is displayed by using the ProcScript instructions in the preDisplay trigger. Table 1. ProcScript Functions Function Description $check Setting $check to True places a checkmark before the menu item. Setting $check to False removes the checkmark before the menu item. If an icon has been defined for the menu item, the checkmark is placed over the icon. $check cannot be used in a menu bar. $disable Setting $disable to True disables the menu item. Setting $disable to False enables the menu item. A disabled menu item is visible but can’t be selected by the user. You can control how a disabled menu is presented in the menu properties. $hide Setting $hide to True hides the menu item. Setting $hide to False shows the menu item. $inlinemenu Menu items of type Dynamic menu are placeholders for menus that you define using ProcScript. You assign the definition of your menu to $inlinemenu . Table 2. ProcScript Statements Statement Description pulldown Use this statement to activate the menu when your Uniface application runs in character mode. pulldown/load Loads a new definition for the application menu bar. Related Links Menu Properties Menu properties enable you to control the appearance of menus using the font, colors, and images. They are applicable only for Windows applications and are defined by the menu logical in the [application] section of the application initialization file (usys.ini). Dynamic Menu Items Dynamic menus contain one or more menu items that are generated at runtime, and inserted in a predetermined location of a drop-down or popup menu. They can be used, for example, to display and open recently accessed objects, list and switch between currently open windows, or provide a pop-up menu that is related to the value of a field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}